message.content:
1. The median follow-up was 45 months.
2. The interquartile range (IQR) for the follow-up was 35–58 months.
3. The median overall survival was 30 months in the twice-daily group.
4. The 95% confidence interval (CI) for overall survival in the twice-daily group was 24–34 months.
5. The median overall survival was 25 months in the once-daily group.
6. The 95% confidence interval (CI) for overall survival in the once-daily group was 21–31 months.
7. The hazard ratio for death in the once-daily group was 1.18.
8. The 95% confidence interval (CI) for the hazard ratio for death in the once-daily group was 0.95–1.45.
9. The p-value for the comparison of death in the once-daily group versus the twice-daily group was 0.14.
